      <h3>Guidelines for Ignite San Diego Presenters</h3>

      <p>An Ignite talk consists of 20 slides that automatically advance every 15 seconds, giving a total talk length of 5 minutes.

      <p>Slides will be presented using a Macintosh computer, running Mac OS Snow Leopard, along with Microsoft PowerPoint 2008 and Keynote '09 (from the iWork app suite).</p>
      
      <h4>Creating your slides</h4>

      <p>Please follow these guidelines when creating your slides:</p>
      
      <ol>
      <li>Save your slides in either Keynote (".key") or PowerPoint (".ppt").</li>
      <li>Keep slides simple. Please refrain from using animations or sounds.</li>
      <li>You must have exactly 20 original slides. Do not duplicate slides.</li>
      <li>Your slides should be designed for 1024x768 resolution.</li>
      <li>When adding images, make sure images are downsized appropriately. If you're using images from a phone or camera, this is especially important.</li>
      <li>Please include your talk name in your slideshow file. (Example: "dutch_ovens_are_awesome_talk.ppt")</li>
      </ol>
      
      <h4>Submitting your slides</h4>

      <p>Please follow these guidelines when submitting your slides:</p>

      <ol>
      <li>Email a copy to <a href="mailto:ignitesandiego@gmail.com">ignitesandiego@gmail.com</a>.</li>
      <li>Post your slides to <a href="http://www.slideshare.net/event/ignite-san-diego">http://www.slideshare.net/event/ignite-san-diego</a> for public viewing.</li>
      </ol>

      <p><strong>Slides must be submitted by 11:59 pm on July 31.</strong></p>
      
      <p>Any questions? <a href="mailto:ignitesandiego@gmail.com">Drop us a line</a>.</p>
    
